<TITLE> Ajker Kagoj shuts down </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 19 (bdnews24.com)  A troubled Bangla-language newspaper, Ajker Kagoj, has stopped its operations from Wednesday. In a statement, the newspaper cited a financial crisis as the reason for shutdown. "The organisation is no longer able to continue its publication due to a financial crisis," the statement said. Ajker Kagoj expressed "gratefulness to readers, writers, advertisers and other well-wishers for their cooperation since 1991". The news organisation said it would make arrangements to pay all dues for journalists and other employees "as soon as possible". bd
